Wash and dry produce. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Drain @corn{1%unit}. 

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, whisk together @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, @tomato paste{1%unit}, @chicken stock concentrate{3%unit}, and @water{1/4%cup}. Microwave until thickened, ~{30-40%seconds}.

Open package of @chopped chicken breast{20%oz} and drain off any excess liquid. Season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #5- to 6-quart slow cooker{}, combine chicken with @Tex-Mex paste{1%unit}, onion, corn, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz}, @black beans{1%unit} and their liquid, cornstarch mixture, and @water{3%cups}; stir until well combined.

> TIP: If the chicken pieces are sticking together, make sure to separate them.

Cover and cook on high until chicken is tender and cooked through, ~{4%hours}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Once soup is ready to serve, roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz} and lightly crush @blue corn tortilla chips{3%oz} in bag.

Serve tortilla soup family style, with cilantro, tortilla chips, @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, and @Mexican cheese blend{1/2%cup} in separate bowls. Let everyone add their own toppings!

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.